# File: tests/features/page-analyze.feature
#
# Generated from: .claude/specs/feature-add-page-analyze-command-for-page-structure-discovery/requirements.md
# Issue: #190

Feature: Page Analyze Command
  As a browser automation engineer starting work on an unfamiliar page
  I want a single command that reveals the page's structure, frameworks, and potential automation challenges
  So that I can choose the right interaction strategy immediately instead of spending 30+ minutes probing the DOM manually

  # --- Happy Path ---

  Scenario: AC1 - Structural summary output
    Given a loaded page with iframes, media elements, overlays, and a known frontend framework
    When I run "agentchrome page analyze"
    Then the JSON output contains an "iframes" array with frame URLs, visibility, and dimensions
    And the JSON output contains a "frameworks" array with detected framework names
    And the JSON output contains an "interactiveElements" object with counts per frame
    And the JSON output contains a "media" array with tag type, source, and playback state
    And the JSON output contains an "overlays" array with selector, dimensions, and z-index
    And the JSON output contains a "shadowDom" object with "present" boolean and "hostCount" number
    And the JSON output contains a "summary" object with aggregate counts and boolean flags

  # --- Alternative Paths ---

  Scenario: AC2 - Frame-scoped analysis
    Given a loaded page with an iframe at index 1 containing interactive elements
    When I run "agentchrome page analyze --frame 1"
    Then the JSON output "scope" field is "frame:1"
    And all element counts and detection results are scoped to frame 1 only
    And the command exits with code 0

  Scenario: AC5 - Cross-origin iframe enumeration
    Given a loaded page with a cross-origin iframe
    When I run "agentchrome page analyze"
    Then the "iframes" array includes an entry with "crossOrigin" set to true
    And the cross-origin iframe entry contains "url", "width", and "height"
    And the interactive element count for the cross-origin iframe is null if inaccessible

  # --- Edge Cases ---

  Scenario: AC3 - Simple page handling
    Given a loaded page with no iframes, overlays, frameworks, media, or shadow DOM
    When I run "agentchrome page analyze"
    Then the JSON output "iframes" is an empty array
    And the JSON output "frameworks" is an empty array
    And the JSON output "media" is an empty array
    And the JSON output "overlays" is an empty array
    And the JSON output "shadowDom" has "present" set to false
    And the JSON output "summary" has "iframeCount" set to 0
    And the JSON output "summary" has "hasOverlays" set to false
    And the command exits with code 0

  Scenario: AC7 - Undetermined output fields use null
    Given a loaded page where some analysis dimensions cannot be determined
    When I run "agentchrome page analyze"
    Then fields that cannot be determined appear as null in the JSON output
    And fields that cannot be determined are not omitted or set to zero
    And the command exits with code 0

  # --- Error Handling ---

  Scenario: AC6 - Invalid frame index error
    Given a loaded page with no iframes
    When I run "agentchrome page analyze --frame 99"
    Then a JSON error is written to stderr with a message about invalid frame index
    And the command exits with a non-zero exit code

  # --- Documentation ---

  Scenario: AC4 - Documentation updated
    When I run "agentchrome examples page"
    Then the output includes an example for "agentchrome page analyze"
    And the output includes an example for "agentchrome page analyze --frame 1"
